not drinking alcohol or smoking cigarettes, it’s my curfew: the strict rule my parents give, compared to their freedom. They have a freedom to choose whatever they want, dress whatever they want, etc. But I was in problem when I wanted to go to the mall with my friends, shopping, or even hanging around. It sounds big, but for me it’s a huge problem. I think it’s sad that in teenagers they can’t do the thing without their parents. They can’t be a boy or a girl and even they are not express their self. Even teenagers in big cities like Jakarta has the same problem, so imagine the situation in a small city where most of their peoples are conservative.
